      • set

        public Entries.SetInvocation set(java.lang.String vm,
                                 java.lang.String dataSet,
                                 java.lang.String key,
                                 java.lang.String value)
        Description copied from interface: Entries
        Creates or updates an entry in a data set. If an entry whose key matches key already exists, it will replace the existing value, otherwise it will create a new entry. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.0.
        Specified by:
        set in interface Entries
        Parameters:
        vm - Identifier of the virtual machine. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: VirtualMachine.
        dataSet - Identifier of the data set. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.vm.DataSet.
        key - The key of the entry to set. A key can be at most 4096 bytes. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.vm.data_sets.Entry.
        value - The value of the entry to set. A value can be at most 1MB.
        Returns:
        instance of Entries.SetInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described set operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
